gomodel:SYNGO_1326  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electrophysiological characterisation of GABAA alpha 2 subunit overexpressed in HEK cells, with WC patch-clamp.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P23576] SyNGO ID 1266 (PMID:11168550, EM). Experimental description: No information on species given, also not in references to methods sections in older papers.\n\n29/6/2018 Pim\n- I have selected 'human' as the species of the expressed protein. Since using a weaker NAS mechanism for annotation correct species assignment is not so important." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1326" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

